From c67c16b018a106e1114c956986e1aa231f53fc77 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rob Woolley <rob.woolley@windriver.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 07:46:01 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Replace catkin build with plain setuptools packaging

Convert genmsg to a standard Python package built with setuptools
using PEP 621 metadata in pyproject.toml:

- Add pyproject.toml with project metadata carried over from
  package.xml, an empy runtime dependency, and pytest configuration
- Move scripts/genmsg_check_deps.py into the package as
  genmsg.check_deps and expose it as a genmsg_check_deps
  console script entry point
- Remove setup.py, CMakeLists.txt, package.xml, and the cmake/
  templates; catkin builds and downstream cmake-based message
  generation are no longer supported

Signed-off-by: Rob Woolley <rob.woolley@windriver.com>
Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
